cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as dividing text into clauses. It could also belong to "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the performance of various systems that have taken part in the shared task. Additionally, it could be categorized under "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) as the task involves automated processing of natural language. "cs.IR" (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category as the task involves identifying and extracting relevant information from text. Finally, "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a possible sub-category as many of the systems that have taken part in the shared task use neural network-based approaches.
